						<summary>

						<p>This is a fragment of an inscription (evidently of a different temple) which seems to register a sale as <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi>, of a piece of land belonging to them in common by the village assembly, to the temple of Tiruvaikundattu-Perumānaḍigal for the gold received by them from a certain Perumāḷ Śātti (of Vēḷūr-kūṟṟam.)</p>						

						</summary>
